# FastSQS

**FastAPI-like, production-ready async SQS message processing for Python.**

[![PyPI version](https://img.shields.io/pypi/v/fastsqs.svg)](https://pypi.org/project/fastsqs/)
[![License: MIT](https://img.shields.io/badge/License-MIT-yellow.svg)](LICENSE)

---

## Version 0.3.0 - Production Ready Features

### ğŸš€ New Enterprise Features

- **Idempotency**: Prevent duplicate message processing with memory or DynamoDB storage
- **Advanced Error Handling**: Exponential backoff, circuit breaker, and DLQ management  
- **Visibility Timeout Management**: Automatic monitoring and extension for long-running processes
- **Parallelization**: Concurrent processing with semaphore-based limiting and thread pools

## Key Features

- ğŸš€ **FastAPI-like API:** Familiar decorator-based routing with automatic type inference
- ğŸ”’ **Pydantic Validation:** Automatic message validation and serialization using SQSEvent models
- ğŸ”„ **Auto Async/Sync:** Write handlers as sync or async functions - framework handles both automatically
- ï¿½ï¸ **Middleware Support:** Built-in and custom middleware for logging, timing, and more
- ğŸ¦¾ **Partial Batch Failure:** Native support for AWS Lambda batch failure responses
- ğŸ”€ **FIFO & Standard Queues:** Full support for both SQS queue types with proper ordering
- ğŸ¯ **Flexible Matching:** Automatic field name normalization (camelCase â†” snake_case)
- ğŸ—ï¸ **Nested Routing:** QueueRouter support for complex routing scenarios
- ğŸ **Type Safety:** Full type hints and editor support throughout

---

## Requirements

- Python 3.8+
- [Pydantic](https://docs.pydantic.dev/) (installed automatically)

